# AICP v71 — Protocol Backlog (repo-backed)

> Scope: **protocol only** (Core + extensions + registries + schemas + fixtures + conformance + profiles + implementer guides).
> Out of scope: platform/enforcer implementations, chat UX, agent internals, hosted trust services.

This backlog translates consumer adoption needs into **repo-shippable** deliverables:
- RFC/Docs (normative where needed)
- Registries
- JSON Schemas
- Golden fixtures (JSONL transcripts)
- Conformance suites + runner checks
- Profiles (bundle suites)
- Implementer guides + adapter templates (no hosted infra)
- Snapshot + release discipline

## Shipped baseline (as of v71)
- Core productized: envelope, hash-chain, message_hash, signature verify, CONTRACT_PROPOSE/ACCEPT, CONTEXT_AMEND, ATTEST_ACTION, RESOLVE_CONFLICT, ERROR.
- Extensions productized: CAPNEG, ENFORCEMENT, POLICY_EVAL, PARTICIPANTS, TOOL_GATING, IDENTITY_LC, DELEGATION, WORKFLOW_SYNC, DISPUTES, SECURITY_ALERT(S), ALERTS, RESUME, OBJECT_RESYNC, DELEGATED_IDENTITY.
- Profiles shipped (still mostly `experimental`): BASE, MEDIATED-BLOCKING, MEDIATED-BLOCKING-OPS, RECEPTION-CHAT, RESUMABLE-SESSIONS, DELEGATED-IDENTITY, WORKFLOW-ORCHESTRATION-DELEGATION.
- Governance: coverage gate, dropins asset sync, snapshot manifest + validator.

